{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Supposed ∈ N, E ⊂ R d is Borel, π i, π: E → R d are Lipschitz and π i → π pointwise with bounded Lipschitz constants on E and f i, f ∈ L 1 (E) with f i → f in L 1 (Q).",
    "Then E f i det Dπ i → E f det Dπ.Suppose Q = [0, 1] d and let Q have the standard orientation given by the basis vectors e 1,..., e d. Let ∂Q stand for the boundary of Q.",
    "Naturally, ∂Q is a non-overlapping union of its faces, each being an oriented (d -1)-manifold.",
    "We use σ for the surface measure on ∂Q.",
    "We denote by Tan ∂Q the unit oriented tangent to ∂Q, whose orientation is induced by the orientation of Q."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Then E f i det Dπ i → E f det Dπ.Suppose Q = [0, 1] d and let Q have the standard orientation given by the basis vectors e 1,..., e d. Let ∂Q stand for the boundary of Q."
  ]
